summary: I usually make a point of watching the Tenth Doctors last episodes, The End of Time Parts 1 and 2, around Christmas. It’s sort...
body:
I usually make a point of watching the Tenth Doctors last episodes, The End of Time Parts 1 and 2, around Christmas. It’s sort of a personal tradition, but I haven’t done so in the past 2-3 years.

As time has gone on with older series and Ten’s tenure becoming more of a blur within the fandom, it’s something I realised I wanted to keep doing to remind me of why he meant so much to me. I remember the last few times I watched the episodes I shed a tear or two, but I decided to watch it tonight and let me tell you I sobbed.

Bawled.

Don’t know what happened, don’t know where it came from. It’s nearly been 10 years and when I realised that I cried harder. Whether it was the nostalgia that hit me or just pure love for the Tenth Doctor, I cried just as hard as the first time I watched it.

I was sad, yes. But I also felt 10 years younger. I felt connected. I felt so much love for a character I have (and let’s just be honest here) devoted a chunk of my life to. A character who changed my life. A character who has just made my life that little bit more fun.

So to all of you sat there thinking I’m ‘too old’ to watch that show again or ‘it seems boring now’ - screw those thoughts.

Go and watch that show that used to make you smile.

Go and watch that episode that makes you cry.

Go and watch that character you love so much.

It is worth it.

summary:
Keys to the Kingdom - Chapter 2
An Aiden Hoynes fic | Start from the beginning
Word Count: 4294
Rating: Explicit
Summary: Aiden...
body:
Keys to the Kingdom - Chapter 2

An Aiden Hoynes fic | Start from the beginning

Word Count: 4294

Rating: Explicit

Summary: Aiden and Carolina both have agendas, and despite their growing passion for each other, they both have their eyes on the prize … or do they?

He stared at her as she waved enthusiastically at Noah and Ruby’s car. She blew an exaggerated kiss, and clutched at her chest.

“Great catch,” Aiden said, and walked into the boy’s bedroom. Handmade paper streamers hung from the ceiling, and large, old-fashioned political maps were carefully taped to the walls. She turned, and her face relaxed from its frenetic joy.

“Clever man,” she said. She loved watching him just … exist. He wriggled his graceful fingers and grabbed one of Noah’s toys, a balsa wood plane that had seen better days.

“It took you a while to get him ready this morning,” he said, riffling through one of Noah’s encyclopedias. It was open on Ecuador. He knew better than to mess with it – the boy would notice.

“He was doing so well, but for the last several days, he’s been clinging. It’s as if he doesn’t want to leave me alone.” Her brow furrowed with worry, and she hugged herself. “His mum’s been away too long, and a few very hasty phone calls isn’t cutting it. He needs her.”

He observed her from the other side of the room. She loved Noah and Ruby, but she was the diametric opposite of Freya. While Freya’s love ran cold, Lina’s love ran red-hot. He looked down at his hands, palms pale and wide, and his mouth filled with saliva. It had been nearly a week since they last came together. His skin called out for her – her sweat, her saliva, her copious cunt juice. The thought made him swell in his trousers, but something scratched underneath the surface of his consciousness. A deeper need. He shook his head. There could be nothing more than what they had now.

He felt her behind him. “What are you thinking?” she said, looking down on him. He rose and walked out of Noah’s bedroom. He didn’t wait or adjust his pace, because he knew she followed. She always did.

They went down several flights of stairs, past the small nest of offices, the kitchen, then the service floor. He looked behind him. She was exactly twelve steps behind, her gaze to to the floor. She was well-trained, but just as soon as they reached the narrow corridor to his private study, her pace quickened, and she walked in the door before him.

Just as the door clicked firmly behind them, they came together, a panting tangle of arms and legs against the hulking ebony desk.

“I missed you-“he said into her mouth, then bit her plump, unpainted lower lip. She yipped, but her muscles went lax with desire.

summary:
So I’m watching the Doctor Who reruns on BBCAmerica and Rise of the Cybermen is on. 
There’s this terrible scene of the cyber...
body:
So I’m watching the Doctor Who reruns on BBCAmerica and Rise of the Cybermen is on.

There’s this terrible scene of the cyber factory where theyre LITERALLY pulling brains out of skulls and attaching them to metal exoskeletons. You know, like you do.

Guess what song is playing in the background? I bet you can’t.

IN THE JUNGLE from the Lion King is playing.

There’s a juxtaposition if I’ve ever seen/heard one.
